00:05:38.780 --> 00:05:40.140
Because the cost was higher.

00:05:40.140 --> 00:05:43.430
If I failed a test in high
school it affected my grades.

00:05:43.430 --> 00:05:46.200
And that affected my chance
of getting into college.

00:05:46.200 --> 00:05:47.930
And I lived in this
really small town

00:05:47.930 --> 00:05:50.720
and I wanted nothing
more than to leave.

00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:55.020
So, I got to the point where
one failure, at one thing,

00:05:55.020 --> 00:05:57.410
would sort of send me
into a spiral of doubt.

00:05:57.410 --> 00:05:59.290
If I failed at a test.

00:05:59.290 --> 00:06:00.920
If I, you know, let a friend down.

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:02.220
If I screwed something up.

00:06:02.220 --> 00:06:03.520
If I was late to something.

00:06:03.520 --> 00:06:05.360
I would kind of get
worked into a frenzy.

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:08.700
And at this point, I wasn't
learning from my failures.

00:06:08.700 --> 00:06:11.310
I just wanted to avoid them.

00:06:11.310 --> 00:06:13.420
And I never examined my failures.

00:06:13.420 --> 00:06:15.780
I didn't forgive myself for them.

00:06:15.780 --> 00:06:18.890
I just got really,
really, angry at myself.

00:06:18.890 --> 00:06:20.810
And I hated myself.

00:06:20.810 --> 00:06:22.650
And my self-esteem just tanked.

00:06:22.650 --> 00:06:26.920 position:56%
