and she would like pet me,

00:08:28.070 --> 00:08:29.370
you know, over the phone.

00:08:29.370 --> 00:08:30.670
And be like, it's going to be okay.

00:08:30.670 --> 00:08:31.970
It's going to be okay.

00:08:31.970 --> 00:08:33.270
Pull it together.

00:08:33.270 --> 00:08:35.890
Right? So, I started realizing,
really quickly, that if I wanted

00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:39.020
to continue to work at the finest
news organization in the world,

00:08:39.020 --> 00:08:42.680
I did not have time to listen
to that voice inside of my head.

00:08:42.680 --> 00:08:44.140
Telling me that I was the worst.

00:08:44.140 --> 00:08:48.770
I did not have time to give it any
attention because I didn't want

00:08:48.770 --> 00:08:51.670
to be thrown out onto the street
outside the Washington Post.

00:08:51.670 --> 00:08:55.600
I couldn't sit there and wallow
in how much I sucked, frankly.

00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:57.870
So, I was going to have
to learn from my failure.

00:08:57.870 --> 00:08:59.380
But not just learn from it.

00:08:59.380 --> 00:09:01.570
I was going to have to get
very comfortable with failure.

00:09:01.570 --> 00:09:04.780
Because I would be failing
again, and again, and again.

00:09:04.780 --> 00:09:07.030
And I could not let
that voice cripple me

00:09:07.030 --> 00:09:09.630
and leave me in a spiral of doubt.

00:09:09.630 --> 00:09:11.630 position:56%
I couldn't let that voice take over.

00:09:11.630 --> 00:09:17.750
So, I started the very, very, very
uncomfortable process of starting

00:09:17.750 --> 00:09:19.660
