00:09:55.020 --> 00:09:57.970
But instead, something
very strange happened.

00:09:57.970 --> 00:09:59.270
I sat in the newsroom.

00:09:59.270 --> 00:10:00.860
I was kind of in the
center of the newsroom.

00:10:00.860 --> 00:10:03.180
And there were all these
reporters and editors around.

00:10:03.180 --> 00:10:04.720
And some of them were
these huge names.

00:10:04.720 --> 00:10:06.020
And they had won Pulitzer Prizes

00:10:06.020 --> 00:10:08.180
and they had movies
based off their books.

00:10:08.180 --> 00:10:10.690
A few of them started coming over.

00:10:10.690 --> 00:10:13.610
And they were like, hey, you
know, you did a really good job.

00:10:13.610 --> 00:10:16.440
And I was like .

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:17.740
. . were you .

00:10:17.740 --> 00:10:19.040
. . are you talking
about the same person?

00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:21.970
Do I have a twin in the room
who knows what she's doing?

00:10:21.970 --> 00:10:23.270
But they were like, no, no, no.

00:10:23.270 --> 00:10:25.950
We heard. We saw.

00:10:25.950 --> 00:10:27.250
But you learned.

00:10:27.250 --> 00:10:28.550
And you got better.

